snippet: Under an agreement, a former high school football player pleaded guilty to a misdemeanor in a sexual assault case whose initial investigation ended with sexual assault charges being dropped.
abstract: Former Maryville, Mo, high school football player Matthew B Barnett, under an agreement, pleads guilty to a misdemeanor in sexual assault of student Daisy Coleman and is sentenced to two years' probation; initial investigation in case drew national outrage when it ended in 2011 with sexual assault charges being dropped.
lead_paragraph: Under an agreement, a former high school football player pleaded guilty to a misdemeanor in a sexual assault case whose initial investigation ended with sexual assault charges being dropped.

headline.main: Sexual Assault Case Yields a Plea Deal in Missouri
headline.print_headline: Sexual Assault Case Yields A Plea Deal in Missouri
